1. Checking if the i-th Bit is Set
(1 << i) & num   → set if result ≠ 0
(num >> i) & 1   → set if result ≠ 0
---------------------------------------
#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

bool ith_bit_set_or_not(int n, int i){
    return (n & (1 << i));
}
int main() {
    int a = 13;
    int i = 2;
    
    cout << ith_bit_set_or_not(a, i);
    
    return 0;
}
________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
2. Setting the i-th Bit
num | (1 << i)
________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
3. Clearing the i-th Bit
num & ~(1 << i)
________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
4. Toggling the i-th Bit
num ^ (1 << i)
________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

